    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-22T01:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-22T01:30:00-05:00" n="319"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/14174: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Linnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-22T14:30:00+08:00"
                            >October 22, 1938—2:30 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 22—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Two cars with Japanese officers and two lorries with Japanese troops came to
                    British and French bridges of Shameen at 2 p.m. today. Japanese officers saluted
                    and shook hands with the British Concession Chief of Police and then went on to
                    the city. Planes are flying low covering the entry.</p>
                <p>Repeated Chungking, Peiping, Hong Kong.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Linnell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
